==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mulier
<hw>Mu"li*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a
woman.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A woman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Lawful issue born in
wedlock, in distinction from an elder brother born of the same parents
before their marriage; a lawful son.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <fld>(Civ.
Law)</fld> <def>A woman; a wife; a mother.</def> <rj><au>Blount.</au>
<au>Cowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mulierly</ent>⟦br⟧
